<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1407" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1407">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/157.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s February 13. Minister for Foreign. Affairs informs me that
                            in view of the objections of the Government of the United States the
                            Duncan railway contract will be withdrawn from the Assembly.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>